{"title": "Crime of the Congo", "description": "A Conan Doyle brings the skills of thorough analysis in his documenting  of the atrocities occurring in the Congo Free State (an area now known as the Democratic Republic of Congo, the area south of the Congo River basin) following the European Berlin Conference 1884-85. \r\nWitness testimonies (chapter 8 and 9 in particular) and reportage is explicit in recounting the killing and torture of indigenous inhabitants , first sanctioned under King Leopold II\u2019s private rule (1885- 1908) and (Doyle evidences) with limited change in structures/systems under the Belgian state\u2019s early rule once it had annexed the Congo Free State to become  the Belgian Congo (1908-1960). \r\nThe attitudes and lives of missionaries, traders and corporate representatives are also explored in relation to the Congo Free State. \r\nThe Crime of the Congo is a non-fiction account by an eminent fiction writer and it serves also as a cautionary tale to humanity. - Summary by Faith Ab\u00ed\u00f3\u0323l\u00e1-Ellison", "duration": 26683, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "467", "name": "Sir Arthur Conan Doyle"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/crimeofthecongo_2512_librivox/crime_congo_2512.jpg", "copyright_year": "1909", "genres": ["Modern (19th C)"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Faith Abiola-Ellison"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Faith Abiola-Ellison"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "redrun"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Larry Wilson"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface and Introduction", "readers": [18573], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/crimeofthecongo_2512_librivox/crimeofthecongo_00_doyle_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1015}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter 1", "readers": [18573], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/crimeofthecongo_2512_librivox/crimeofthecongo_01_doyle_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1359}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 2", "readers": [18573], "p